A simple game of Pong for an Arduino Uno, Sparkfun's Color LCD Shield (https://www.sparkfun.com/products/9363), and a potentiometer. The LCD Screen's buttons aren't used, but the potentiometer is read by Analog Pin 3. 

Before using this program, make sure to download Peter Davenport's ColorLCD  library here: https://github.com/downloads/jimblom/ColorLCDShield/ColorLCDShield-July-16-2012.zip. 